    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 1.3L 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains its factory-spec apex seal integrity with documented high-compression figures across all rotor faces. The chassis retains its legendary 50:50 weight distribution and remains structurally uncompromised, supported by original double-wishbone suspension components and a crisp-shifting 5-speed manual transmission paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Meticulously maintained with a full silicone vacuum line refresh and zero thermal degradation on the wiring harness, this FD delivers linear power delivery and telepathic handling. The paint depth is consistent throughout, reflecting its sheltered life and mechanical preservation.",
